case_circumstances: The decedent is a currently unidentified Caucasian female, estimated to be in her 40s. On the morning of 10/16/81, her burned body was found in the rear alley of a retail office supply store located at 1753 Garnet Avenue by an employee of the business.  San Diego Police Department officers responded to the scene and found the decedent in a supine position on the ground among burned papers and debris.  The anterior chest and truck, right arm, and posterior trunk and right leg were charred.  Stab wounds were noted on the neck and homicide detectives were called to the scene.
